# Glamour PDF - Environment Variables

## Required Environment Variables

### Backend (.env)
```bash
# Groq API Key (Required for AI functionality)
GROQ_API_KEY=your_groq_api_key_here

# Server Port (Optional - defaults to 3000)
PORT=3000
```

## Deployment URLs

### Backend (Render)
- Production: `https://machine-learning-ai-rag-basics.onrender.com`
- Local: `http://localhost:3000`

### Frontend
The frontend automatically detects the environment:
- When running on `localhost` or `127.0.0.1` → Uses `http://localhost:3000`
- When running on any other domain → Uses `https://machine-learning-ai-rag-basics.onrender.com`

## Setup Instructions

### Local Development
1. Clone the repository
2. Copy `.env.example` to `.env`
3. Add your `GROQ_API_KEY` to `.env`
4. Run `npm install`
5. Run `npm start` to start the backend server
6. Open `frontend/index.html` in your browser

### Production (Render Backend)
1. Ensure your backend is deployed to Render
2. Set `GROQ_API_KEY` environment variable in Render dashboard
3. Deploy frontend to any static hosting (Vercel, Netlify, GitHub Pages, etc.)
4. The frontend will automatically connect to the Render backend

## Updating Backend URL
If you need to change the production backend URL, edit `frontend/index.html`:
```javascript
const API_BASE_URL = window.location.hostname === 'localhost' || window.location.hostname === '127.0.0.1'
    ? 'http://localhost:3000'
    : 'https://your-new-backend-url.com'; // ← Change this line
```
